  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@vvo \n\n> Good, in the end it was not so much boilerplate code to add to test this bug. In the future we might just have a BaseWidget to break a little bit this redundant logic we have (cssClasses)\n\nWell, yes and no, because here we were just missing a `var` keyword, which would have been missing  even if we embedded all the logic in a common function, the issue was present in all widgets.\n\nThere's a choice to make, and a little bit of consistency to have here. Do you really want to unit test everything ? If yes, we can't test only once for code that is copy/pasted everywhere. But then we shouldn't only add tests on bug-fixes, but also on every `feat` and `chore` PR.\n\nBy the way, I didn't add tests for widgets that I fixed but didn't have a test file.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-02T09:18:33Z",
